If you want to know how much you can understand a anime or a video game based on your level, you can use links and tutorials from this spreadsheet. Go into the deck's Option - Description panel to delete this text.

I should buy an electronic notebook.

I've read it. It's a good book!

His youngest son's in your year, Tsukishima. You don't know him? He is?!

You met a prince from one of your books?
Come on, Yuko, you heard his name. Tell us!
You want to know, but you don't...

This formula will be on the mid-term, so remember it!

Well, I'll do the best I can.

... in search of the treasure of lapis lazuli!

I was out there calling you in my head.

Amasawa Seiji... what's he like? Wonder if he's nice.
Do you know who this 'Amasawa' is?
If I have to stand in the sun I get more freckles!
Yeah, yeah... all right, out of here, both of you.
West Ginia, my mother the mountain...
That's not bad. Yes, it is.

Come on, Tsukishima! Throw it over here.

It was the same thing last year.
Yes! It was miso! Boy, was it heavy!

You don't have to read them! Take the paper-clip off.

What a hill! How far up is he going?
I never knew there was a place like this way up here...
That's all right. Look around all you want.

So you're a young lady who knows about dwarfs, are you?
The light shines on the glass. Come up here.

That's why they both look so sad...
Only about five minutes, though. Oh, no!
I've got to be at the library!
Sure... but go left to get to the library!

I'll buy something. You will? Thanks, then.

Got a feeling itll take me...

... now I've written it I know.
... but Seiji's getting further and further ahead.

When Seiji finished his first violin, we had ramen noodles.

I was a student. He looked so melancholic...
I asked the owner to sell him to me.
The Baron had a lover, and he wouldn't separate them.
He was waiting for her to come back from being repaired... ... at the doll-maker's shop.

Then a lady friend of mine...
